---
    <Layout title="Dryer Igniter  Replacement Cost - Ultimate Guide" description="Navigate dryer igniter replacement cost with our comprehensive guide. Find a reliable technicians, and make informed decisions. Call: (323) 870-4790">
 

 
  <Container>
    <main style="max-width: 1440px; margin: 0 auto">
      <h1>
        <span class="animate-charcter">Dryer Igniter Replacement Cost</span>
      </h1>

      <div class="two-col-grid">
        <div class="col-one">
          <img
            class="img-header"
            src="/images/lg-dryer-repair.webp"
            width="500"
            height="500"
            alt="Dryer Igniter Replacement Cost"
          />

          
        </div>

        <div class="col-two">
          <p>
            The igniter in a dryer is a critical component that ignites the gas
            used to heat the air for drying clothes. When the igniter fails, the
            dryer will not heat up, leaving your clothes damp after a cycle.
            This guide provides information on the costs and considerations
            involved in replacing a dryer igniter.
          </p>
          <h2>LG Dryer Igniter Replacement Cost</h2>
          <p>
            At our company, Same Day Appliance Repair, we keep transparent
            pricing. The dryer igniter replacement cost is $220, excluding
            parts. Initially, technicians will diagnose the specific issue for
            the service fee of $89. During this visit, he will detail the
            problem and provide a breakdown of costs. If you opt for the repair,
            the service fee is waived, and you only pay for the repair itself.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2>Factors Affecting Dryer Igniter Cost</h2>
      <p>
        &bull; Dryer Model: The make and model of your dryer can significantly
        affect the cost of replacement parts. High-end or less common models may
        have more expensive igniters.<br /><br />
        &bull;Igniter Type: There are different types of igniters, such as glow bar
        or spark igniters, and their costs can vary.<br /><br />
        &bull;Service Fees: Labor costs for professional installation can differ
        based on your location and the service provider.
      </p>
      <h2>Average Replacement Dryer Igniter Costs</h2>
      <p>
        &bull; Parts: The cost of a new igniter typically ranges from $30 to
        $100, depending on the type and model of your dryer.<br /><br />
        &bull; Labor: Installation costs is $220.<br /><br />
        &bull; Total Cost: The total expense for replacing a dryer igniter can vary
        from $250 to $320.
      </p>
      <h2>DIY Replacement vs. Professional Service</h2>
      <p>
        &bull; DIY Replacement: If you are experienced in appliance repair, you
        may choose to replace the igniter yourself, saving on labor costs. It's
        crucial to follow safety guidelines and consult the dryer's manual.<br
        /><br />
        &bull; Professional Service: Hiring a professional is advisable for those
        unfamiliar with appliance repair. Professionals ensure proper installation
        and testing of the igniter.
      </p>
      <h2>Selecting a Repair Service</h2>
      <p>
        &bull; Experience and Qualifications: Choose a technician with proven
        experience in dryer repairs and necessary qualifications.<br /><br />
        &bull; Warranty and Service Guarantees: Opt for repair services that offer
        warranties on parts and labor to secure your investment.<br /><br />
        &bull; Customer Reviews: Research and select a service provider with positive
        customer feedback and reliability.
      </p>
      <h2>Conclusion</h2>
      <p>
        Replacing the igniter in your dryer is essential for maintaining its
        performance and efficiency. By understanding the costs involved and
        selecting the right approach for replacement, you can ensure your dryer
        remains functional and effective for drying your clothes.
      </p>

    </main>
  </Container>
 

